top.value: Abana b’Imana (children of God) project seeks to improve and benefit the lives of orphans in AEBR Youth in Rwanda. With the help of volunteers and through camps, trainings and groups of hope, we seek to empower youth and to give orphans hope for a better life. In Rwanda, having a family is a big part of your social and financial support system. Therefore, orphans are a vulnerable group who are in general risk, both socially, economically, and emotionally. By training volunteers to engage with this vulnerable group we both improve the organizational capacity and volunteer base of AEBR Youth, and give the orphans and entry point into the church and local society.

A Danish project group in Ung Mosaik (UM) has due to previous trips to Nakuru, Kenya and contact with the potential partner, The Free Pentecostal Fellowship in Kenya Youth (FPFK Youth), a desire to determine whether a formalized partnership between the two organizations can be established The project group has seen a great need of support and help in the area of Nakuru where FPFK Youth headquarters is located FPFK Youth?s initiative to empower and educate the local youth has sparked an interest in the Danish group to support this objective in order to have an even greater impact and sustainability FPFK Youth has a vision to build up capacity in at-risk youth to become active agents in their own lives, instead of being passive victims of poverty and injustice and to participate actively in their local communities Through activities, workshops and meetings during a Partner Identification trip our goal is to determine if a future sustainable partnership is possible The dream scenario is to lay the ground of a fruitful partnership that supports and empowers the leaders of FPFK Youth to have a greater impact in their community

After 4 years of cooperation, we want to discuss new aspects of our partnership.  Due to corona we want to see if we could find a way to arrange the local forum day from our Partnership Project. We still think this activity is important for our partnership. We want to involve the elected officials of Aalborg and F?s to create other channels of collaboration between the various actors of the two cities.  Another aspect of our partnership is democracy. Both AY and CSworks daily with democracy and the involment of youngpeople in community life and the promotion of youth participation through participatory democracy mechanisms and citizen participation. For this project, we want to involve the peer education group ?Aalborg Youth council? in our partnership so the peer education approach can combine the peer education group ?Sexualisterne? with the ?Youth council in Aalborg and the local youth council in COS. We want to train and support its organs and the use of peer education as a means of training and sensitizing young people for effective participation in local governance.

After 5 years of cooperation and a newly finished partnership project, our aim is to use this opportunity to reflect upon the lessons learned this far and together define and match our visions and hopes for the future of our partnership. This will be done through discussions and workshops between the members of the three organisations leading up to the development of a new partnership strategy and agreement. In addition, we would like to secure a basis for our future work, and improve the conditions for this, by having workshops in communication and handovers, building up the capacity in each organisations to ensure the strength and sustainability of the IMUNZI partnership.

After carrying out a successful pilot project in 2022 between Ung Mosaik and ECY, the two organizations desire a preparatory study to investigate the opportunities for a future project. The target group and three main focuses of a future project are:  1. Organizational development through focusing on strengthening the mental health of the leaders and training new leaders. 2. Activities and classes for the youth of Bourj Hammoud. 3. Advocacy with a focus on ethnic and gender equality, learning youth to use their voice, and changing the view of Syrian refugees in society.  Through interviews, focus groups, and workshops with our target group, the teenagers, and the leaders we will reach our objectives. During the preparatory study, we seek to clarify how to draw on experiences from the pilot project and prepare to apply for a partnership project.

After the massive crackdown of civil society organizations in Belarus, youth organizations are facing a variety of challenges, including security, administrative and capacity related problems that hinder their abilities to conduct their activities in the country or the exile. To provide help for Belarusian youth organizations undergoing structural changes and security threats, build capacities on active citizenship among Belarusian youth and ensure sustainable and uninterrupted activities of Belarusian youth CSOs, this project includes several activities providing a well-rounded approach. The Organizational Clinic session aims at informing organizations on the article 193-1 and its implications, next steps after liquidation, and fundraising; Small-Scale Pool provides consultations and opportunities to acquire digital and physical tools according to their demands to increase their administrative and security capacity; and Training of Trainers will result in the establishment of a pool of trainers ensuring the continuous educational capacity across organizations.

Ashipti Denmark works toward educating young people and citizens of the immense strain Non-Commutable-Diseases have on society, public health care, and most importantly on individuals. With our previous experience in working with partnerships and on NCD prevention in Uganda, we hope to start a new partnership in Ghana. Our plan is to conduct a Partnership-Identification, in-volving a visit in Ghana for approximately  10 days where we will have meetings and workshops with the organisation Ghana FGMSA that we have been in contact with as well as other relevant stakeholders to get a proper understanding of the context and identify other possibilities of future partnerships.   The main goal is to find out if Ashipti Denmark and Ghana FGMSA match in regard to common values, goals and working methods and if so, find a common ground to start a new partnership working with NDC prevention in Ghana since NCDs is an increasing problem in Ghana, this would preferably be in the form of a preparatory study or pilot project. The focus on a new project be-sides NCDs, would be capacity building with both partners involved.
